{"title_page": "Confederation of the Polish Crown", "text_new": "{{Infobox political party\n| name = Confederation of the Polish Crown\n| logo = File:Confederation of the Polish Crown Logo.png\n| colorcode = #DAA520\n| leader1_title = Chairman\n| leader1_name = [[Grzegorz Braun]]\n| leader3_title = Vice-Chairman\n| leader3_name = Roman Fritz\n| leader5_title = General Secretary\n| leader5_name = W\u0142odzimierz Skalik\n| foundation = 7 September 2019\n| ideology = [[Absolute monarchy|Absolute monarchism]]<br>[[Laissez-faire]]<br>[[Paleolibertarianism]]<br>[[Polish nationalism]]<br>[[Libertarian]]<br>[[Traditionalist Catholicism|Traditionalism]]<br>[[Euroscepticism#Hard Euroscepticism|Hard Euroscepticism]]\n| headquarters = [[Cz\u0119stochowa]], [[Poland]]\n| national = [[Confederation Liberty and Independence]]\n| international = \n| website = {{url|https://konfederacjakoronypolskiej.pl/}}\n| country = Poland\n| native_name = Konfederacja Korony Polskiej\n| native_name_lang = pl\n| split = \n| dissolved = \n| successor = \n| position = [[Far-right politics|Far-right]]\n| colors = \n| european = \n| europarl = ''none''\n| seats1_title = [[Sejm of the Republic of Poland|Sejm]]\n| seats1 = {{composition bar|1|460|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n| seats2_title = [[Senate of the Republic of Poland|Senate]]\n| seats2 = {{composition bar|0|100|hex=}}\n| seats3_title = [[European Parliament]]\n| seats3 = {{composition bar|0|51|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n| seats4_title = [[Voivodeship sejmik|Regional assemblies]]\n| seats4 = {{composition bar|0|552|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n| leader2_title = \n| leader2_name = \n| secretary = \n}}\n'''Confederation of the Polish Crown (KKP)''' ({{lang-pl|Konfederacja Korony Polskiej}}) is a [[monarchism|monarchist]], [[Libertarian]] and [[Hard Euroscepticism|hard Eurosceptic]] [[List of political parties in Poland|political party in Poland]] established in 2019 by [[Grzegorz Braun]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pch24.pl/konfederacja-korony-polskiej---oficjalny-start-partii-grzegorza-brauna-,70718,i.html|title=Konfederacja Korony Polskiej \u2013 oficjalny start partii Grzegorza Brauna|website=Pch24.pl}}</ref> The party's goals are to \"fight for the good of Poland, secure the sovereignty of the Polish State, defend Poland's Catholic faith, ensure that Polish families are prosperous, and help shape social life based on the principles of Latin civilization.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://konfederacjakoronypolskiej.pl/|title=Konfederacja Korony Polskiej}}</ref>\n\nSince its formation, the party has been in a coalition with [[KORWiN]] and the [[National Movement (Poland)|National Movement]] called [[Confederation KORWiN Braun Liroy Nationalists|Confederation]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://polskatimes.pl/konfederacja-korwin-liroy-braun-narodowcy-zaprezentowano-nazwe-i-logo-znamy-szczegoly/ar/13923215|title=Konfederacja KORWiN, Liroy, Braun, Narodowcy. Zaprezentowano nazw\u0119 i logo. Znamy szczeg\u00f3\u0142y|last=Rogacin|first=Kacper|date=2019-02-27|website=polskatimes.pl|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-05-06}}</ref> It won a seat during the [[2019 Polish parliamentary election]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wybory.gov.pl/sejmsenat2019/pl/wyniki/kandydat/1300018/sejm/okr/23|title=Wybory do Sejmu i Senatu Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej 2019 r.|website=wybory.gov.pl}}</ref>\n\nParty leader Grzegorz Braun was a candidate in the [[2020 Confederation presidential primary]].<ref>https://twitter.com/GrzegorzBraun_/status/1196419269011165184</ref> He lost to [[Krzysztof Bosak]] during the final round of voting and then immediately endorsed his candidacy.<ref>https://wiadomosci.radiozet.pl/Polska/Polityka/Krzysztof-Bosak-kandydatem-Konfederacji-na-prezydenta-Polski-pokonal-Grzegorza-Brauna</ref>\n\n== Election results ==\n=== Sejm ===\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n!Election year\n!Votes\n!%\n!Rank\n!Seats\n|-\n![[2019 Polish parliamentary election|2019]]\n| 1,256,953\n| 6.81%\n| 5th\n|{{composition bar|1|460|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" |<small>As part of [[Confederation Liberty and Independence]], which won 11 seats in total.</small>\n|}\n\n===Presidential===\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Election year\n! rowspan=2|Candidate\n! colspan=2|1st round\n! colspan=2|2nd round\n|-\n! # of overall votes\n! % of overall vote\n! # of overall votes\n! % of overall vote\n|-\n! [[2020 Polish presidential election|2020]]\n| ''Supporting [[Krzysztof Bosak]]''\n| \n| \n| \n| \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Polish political parties}}\n{{Poland-party-stub}}\n\n[[Category:2019 establishments in Poland]]\n[[Category:Anti-Zionism in Europe]]\n[[Category:Anti-Zionist political parties]]\n[[Category:Catholic political parties]]\n[[Category:Catholicism and far-right politics]]\n[[Category:Conservative parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Eurosceptic parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Far-right political parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Monarchism in Poland]]\n[[Category:Monarchist parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2019]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Polish nationalist parties]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox political party\n| name = Confederation of the Polish Crown\n| logo = File:Confederation of the Polish Crown Logo.png\n| colorcode = #DAA520\n| leader1_title = Chairman\n| leader1_name = [[Grzegorz Braun]]\n| leader3_title = Vice-Chairman\n| leader3_name = Roman Fritz\n| leader5_title = General Secretary\n| leader5_name = W\u0142odzimierz Skalik\n| foundation = 7 September 2019\n| ideology = [[Absolute monarchy|Absolute monarchism]]<br>[[Laissez-faire]]<br>[[Paleolibertarianism]]<br>[[Polish nationalism]]<br>[[Reactionary|Reactionarism]]<br>[[Traditionalist Catholicism|Traditionalism]]<br>[[Euroscepticism#Hard Euroscepticism|Hard Euroscepticism]]\n| headquarters = [[Cz\u0119stochowa]], [[Poland]]\n| national = [[Confederation Liberty and Independence]]\n| international = \n| website = {{url|https://konfederacjakoronypolskiej.pl/}}\n| country = Poland\n| native_name = Konfederacja Korony Polskiej\n| native_name_lang = pl\n| split = \n| dissolved = \n| successor = \n| position = [[Far-right politics|Far-right]]\n| colors = \n| european = \n| europarl = ''none''\n| seats1_title = [[Sejm of the Republic of Poland|Sejm]]\n| seats1 = {{composition bar|1|460|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n| seats2_title = [[Senate of the Republic of Poland|Senate]]\n| seats2 = {{composition bar|0|100|hex=}}\n| seats3_title = [[European Parliament]]\n| seats3 = {{composition bar|0|51|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n| seats4_title = [[Voivodeship sejmik|Regional assemblies]]\n| seats4 = {{composition bar|0|552|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n| leader2_title = \n| leader2_name = \n| secretary = \n}}\n'''Confederation of the Polish Crown (KKP)''' ({{lang-pl|Konfederacja Korony Polskiej}}) is a [[monarchism|monarchist]], [[reactionary|reactionist]] and [[Hard Euroscepticism|hard Eurosceptic]] [[List of political parties in Poland|political party in Poland]] established in 2019 by [[Grzegorz Braun]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pch24.pl/konfederacja-korony-polskiej---oficjalny-start-partii-grzegorza-brauna-,70718,i.html|title=Konfederacja Korony Polskiej \u2013 oficjalny start partii Grzegorza Brauna|website=Pch24.pl}}</ref> The party's goals are to \"fight for the good of Poland, secure the sovereignty of the Polish State, defend Poland's Catholic faith, ensure that Polish families are prosperous, and help shape social life based on the principles of Latin civilization.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://konfederacjakoronypolskiej.pl/|title=Konfederacja Korony Polskiej}}</ref>\n\nSince its formation, the party has been in a coalition with [[KORWiN]] and the [[National Movement (Poland)|National Movement]] called [[Confederation KORWiN Braun Liroy Nationalists|Confederation]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://polskatimes.pl/konfederacja-korwin-liroy-braun-narodowcy-zaprezentowano-nazwe-i-logo-znamy-szczegoly/ar/13923215|title=Konfederacja KORWiN, Liroy, Braun, Narodowcy. Zaprezentowano nazw\u0119 i logo. Znamy szczeg\u00f3\u0142y|last=Rogacin|first=Kacper|date=2019-02-27|website=polskatimes.pl|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-05-06}}</ref> It won a seat during the [[2019 Polish parliamentary election]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wybory.gov.pl/sejmsenat2019/pl/wyniki/kandydat/1300018/sejm/okr/23|title=Wybory do Sejmu i Senatu Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej 2019 r.|website=wybory.gov.pl}}</ref>\n\nParty leader Grzegorz Braun was a candidate in the [[2020 Confederation presidential primary]].<ref>https://twitter.com/GrzegorzBraun_/status/1196419269011165184</ref> He lost to [[Krzysztof Bosak]] during the final round of voting and then immediately endorsed his candidacy.<ref>https://wiadomosci.radiozet.pl/Polska/Polityka/Krzysztof-Bosak-kandydatem-Konfederacji-na-prezydenta-Polski-pokonal-Grzegorza-Brauna</ref>\n\n== Election results ==\n=== Sejm ===\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n!Election year\n!Votes\n!%\n!Rank\n!Seats\n|-\n![[2019 Polish parliamentary election|2019]]\n| 1,256,953\n| 6.81%\n| 5th\n|{{composition bar|1|460|hex={{#DAA520}}}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" |<small>As part of [[Confederation Liberty and Independence]], which won 11 seats in total.</small>\n|}\n\n===Presidential===\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Election year\n! rowspan=2|Candidate\n! colspan=2|1st round\n! colspan=2|2nd round\n|-\n! # of overall votes\n! % of overall vote\n! # of overall votes\n! % of overall vote\n|-\n! [[2020 Polish presidential election|2020]]\n| ''Supporting [[Krzysztof Bosak]]''\n| \n| \n| \n| \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Polish political parties}}\n{{Poland-party-stub}}\n\n[[Category:2019 establishments in Poland]]\n[[Category:Anti-Zionism in Europe]]\n[[Category:Anti-Zionist political parties]]\n[[Category:Catholic political parties]]\n[[Category:Catholicism and far-right politics]]\n[[Category:Conservative parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Eurosceptic parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Far-right political parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Monarchism in Poland]]\n[[Category:Monarchist parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2019]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Polish nationalist parties]]\n", "name_user": "Odoacer Rex", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Confederation_of_the_Polish_Crown"}
